<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-03-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="56" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d56">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23700/7.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-31"><hi rend="italic">March 31,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Wilson informs Minister Beaupré that the extradition papers for
                            Knepper, referred to in legation’s telegram of March 31, will be sent on
                            Saturday.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>